node.text:
Do MORE. Be MORE. Give MORE. 

My heart is full. 

Impromptu group photo. 

3 hours of extroverting so far and I feel like I’ve been run over by an entire bus 🤣🤣

But my love and gratitude right now 😭 I’m so emotional seeing these people. 

I said everyone get behind me for the photo and then have car earners in front. 

This group of people was just standing around and I’m like what the heck…get behind…

Then I realized we have almost 70 car earners at this event 😭😭😭😭😭😭

It’s super cool to be on top. IT IS ABSOLUTELY BREATHTAKING to take so many with you. 

My heart could burst. Not even 4 years yet…

First event back from the pandemic. Just. All the feels.

Are you here? Don’t forget to say hi! I’m not hugging but I’m totally taking photos. 

#bosslee

node.text:
Why network marketing?

Magic moments. 

Brooke was trying to get me to the airport like an hour and a half early for our flight to Kentucky today and I was disinterested 🤣🤣🤣

I reached out to my friend and business partner and asked if he had room on a jet. Uh. LOL. This jet is a 737 hahahahahahh it flies globally. 

Today, it flew to Kentucky where we landed and I took Brian’s Beeeeaaaauuutiful Bentley for the week. 

Brooke goes “b’s everywhere! For me!!”

When I started mentoring and coaching Brooke she told me she doesn’t get on planes. She said she would never fly. 

Oh my, how your life can change when you’re coachable and don’t give up when it’s hard. 

Now we’re at a Brazilian steakhouse grubbing and hanging out with our best friends 😉 ❤️ 

Do you ever want to fly private? 
#bosslee

That’s totally acceptable.

node.text:
Why network marketing? The people.

This coming weekend will be our first event back since 2019.

i’m not gonna be the one to sit on the Internet and lie to you about how excited I am to go. I want to stay home. 

however, my God do I love these people.

I remember the first time that I heard somebody talk about promoting events. I skill set I definitely did not have. It was my now good friend Matt Morris at the six-figure summit with Eric Worre. 

He said something like promoting events is the highest paid skill set you can learn in all of business. if I’m nothing else I’m extremely coachable.

In 2018 we decided to start to have our own team events. In April 2019 our second team event had 811 attendees from around the world.

You could say I lost a couple hundred thousand dollars LOL but I’m pretty sure it’s safe to say I made all of that back and some.

it was at the second event that I decided it was a goal of mine someday to train our team at Dallas Cowboys Stadium after seeing my friend that I mentioned above doing that for his company.

I don’t know when the world will settle down and become its official new normal, but I can promise you I look forward to seeing your smiling faces that change my life every day in person, many for the first time, in just a few short days. 

swipe the carousel to see how we’ve grown.

are you looking forward to events?

Drop a 😯 if the growth is cool to you!

#bosslee

node.text:
It started 4 years ago today. 

A phone call from @lisagrossmann with a “yeah, ok, get a job making $200k a month good luck with that” and a @curtisbroome421 is booking your flight now!

A not so subtle “get on a plane” from @ericworre 

A “I like her I think she’s telling the truth. I want to protect her” from @terry.lacore 

A “we don’t do deals. If you can build it then build it” from @brianundy 

I didn’t know what I was going to do 4 years ago. I just knew I wasn’t who anyone was trying to say I was. 

I didn’t expect only the original 8 to follow. 

I was shaken. I was rattled. I was nervous. But I’ve never backed down. Not when I knew I wouldn’t be the last one hurt if I didn’t stand up and fight for what was right. 

It’s been 4 years. It’s been hundreds of millions of dollars in sales. 

It’s been 140 car earners ($50,000k/month businesses)

It’s been nearly 1,000,000 customers.

It’s been thousands of personal recruits: 

It’s been AN ABSOLUTE GOD SEND. 

4 years ago I had one stream of income and it was taken from me.

Today I have over a dozen.

God doesn’t give you what you can’t handle. Start seeing your greatest tragedies as your set up for your biggest blessings.

The Empire never fell. We simple changed vehicles and are now 6x bigger (and growing) than anything I’ve ever built in business before. 

You cannot stop a woman who puts on the full armor of God. 

If you believe your comeback is coming, too, drop me a ❤️ below 

Happy Phoenix anniversary to me. 

#bosslee
